  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of our study was to investigate whether preoperative skin cleaning on face, neck,
      and chest with chlorhexidine could reduce suture contamination of C. acnes in arthroscopic
      rotator cuff repair. We hypothesized that preoperative skin cleaning on face, neck and chest
      with chlorhexidine can reduce C. acnes contamination on sutures in arthroscopic rotator cuff
      repair.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
